  "text": "Adapty docs frontmatter rule (now codified in CLAUDE.md frontmatter schema section + editor skill SKILL.md Area 8 review check and \"Writing a Full Article\" composition rule): do NOT add `keywords:` unless the user explicitly asks. Keywords drive doc search; extra ones pollute results. When writing/editing, leave keywords out (or untouched if present). If asked, keep to a few specific terms.\n\nContext: virtual currency feature docs being prepped in advance (3 dashboard pages: virtual-currencies root, create-virtual-currency, vc-balance under Products & offers in tutorial.json). Design spec was retrievable via the api.anthropic.com/v1/design/h/<id> handoff URL — it returns a gzipped tar of the whole design project (chats/, project/uploads/*.md with Use Cases + Functional Requirements, project/src/*.jsx mockups). WebFetch can't render it (binary) but saves the .bin; `tar xzf` it. Much richer than the claude.ai/design share link (403).",
